abstract: What makes Nokia’s N76 smartphone has a powerful processor and an operating system that lets it run a number of programs including one that reads Microsoft Office files.
snippet: What makes Nokia’s N76 smartphone has a powerful processor and an operating system that lets it run a number of programs including one that reads Microsoft Office files.
lead_paragraph: With all the talk of the iPhone you might think that Apple was the only company creating fancy new cellphones. Remember Nokia? This Finnish company makes the N76, a smartphone masquerading as a high-fashion accessory.

headline.main: Nokia, Without Fanfare, Introduces a Superphone Without Contract Obstacles
headline.print_headline: Nokia, Without Fanfare, Introduces a Superphone Without Contract Obstacles
